Soo... today was the Puffy AmiYumi concert in Davis sq. It was planned to start at 7:00 pm, so me, sakura, & momo went around 6:00.  When we got there we went to the stand where they were selling merch (tshirts, tourbooks, wristbands, cds, fans, etc...) I bought a fan and a wristband... Okay.. next, we went to our seats, unfortunately they were not the best... (stuck in the balcony in the back right =.=) Anyways.. at 7:00pm some random opening act came out.. never heard of them nor want to hear anymore of them-- lets just say they were-- eehh-- no comment. they werent even japanese u.u ... they finally finished after like a 1/2 hour, then it took another 1/2 hour to set things up and move the other bands stuff outta the way. The most random ppl showed up for it =.= urr i dont even wanna try explaining them butthe majority were random kids with 'otaku' shirts on... ANYWAYS... around 8:00, Ami and Yumi finally came out ^o^.. i wanted their outfit sooo bad... they played a few songs, which btw where hard to see due to the bad seats and the large ppl obstructing the view >.< ... When they went to talk, they had everything written out on flash cards.. it was pretty funny.. they eventually gave up on the english and started speaking in japanese, asking all the japanese members in the audiance to translate for them... due to my poor japanese skills, i only picked up like 2 words of what they were saying >.< *hits self for not studying harder*... they went on for most of the concert, i wanted to take pictures soo bad but the ppl that worked at the theatre wouldnt get away from us, and since you werent supposed to take any pictures, i only left w/ 3, one of them hopefully including ami and yumi. Their next break was funny, they started to say how they found out about how things like clam chowder and dunkin donuts were native to boston, so they asked the crowd if there were any other places... so, which i have no idea why (stupid ppl >.=) tons of ppl in the audiance yell "crispy cream' and "starbucks"... after that discussion, they began speaking in japanese which would be interupped by a "by the way..." ..."have you visited puffyamiyumi.com" and "have you seen the hi hi puffy amiyumi show?", which was also funny cuz they said they had never really seen it because they play the show in the US, south america,Europe, and some of asia... but NOT in JAPAN!! xD 
After, they went on with the show for a few more songs, ending it with either teen titans or their theme song.. i forget... but after a couple minutes break, the croud started to stomp their feet and all yell "PUFFY!!" Sooo... they came back on the stage for their encore... in which they told the crowd how they recently got to meet green day and how they were fans of them. they asked the crowd if they liked green day as most of the crowd goes "yea" me and my freinds were like "uhh.. NO.. eww" >.<  and then they played a green day cover song (i forget which song) and finally ended the show with one last song and a bow with their band ^-^
Overall, it was a pretty good show and im glad i got to see them, (especially since they announced it was their last show in boston)although i wish it was Dir en grey or something, but puffy's cool too, ne?
